      h1 CSSTransitionGroup Pros and Cons
      
      h2 Pros
      ul
        li Nice to keep styles and animations together
        li 
          | You can use 
          a(href="https://github.com/postcss/autoprefixer") Autoprefixer 
          | as part of your build

      h2 Cons
      ul
        li Batch updates can cause transitions to fail
        li May cause CSS bloat
        li Defining sequences using time measurements rather than callbacks can produce unexpected behaviour
        li 
          | Risk of 
          i magic numbers


    .step.slide.filler(data-x=w*10)
      h1 TransitionGroup

      ul 
        li Runs functions on child components before/after mount/unmount
        li Usually requires the definition of two components
        li 
          code componentWillEnter(callback)
          br/
          code componentDidEnter()
          br/
          code componentWillLeave(callback)
          br/
          code componentDidLeave()

      p.footnote
        a(href="http://facebook.github.io/react/docs/animation.html#low-level-api-reacttransitiongroup") React Docs - ReactTransitionGroup


